ly widespread use in the Middle Ages, and increased greatly in popularity in the 18th century and again in the 1990s. In Ireland it serves as an Anglicized form of Irish Luíseach ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lucy Chester was born in 1070, in Spalding, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Robert FitzRainfred de Rumilly. She died in 1136, in Chester, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 66."},"et":{"1070–1136":"1070–1136","1070–1096":"1070–1096","1092–1112":"1092–1112","1136":"1136","1112":"1112","1096":"1096","1070":"1070","1092":"1092","Skipton, Yorkshire, England":"Skipton, Yorkshire, England","Chester, Cheshire, England":"Chester, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Spalding, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Spalding, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Basset, Lot-Et-Garonne, Aquitaine, France":"Basset, Lot-et-Garonne, Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1070–1136":"1070–1136","1070–1096":"1070–1096","1092–1112":"1092–1112","1136":"1136","1112":"1112","1096":"1096","1070":"1070","1092":"1092","Skipton, Yorkshire, England":"Skipton, Yorkshire, England","Chester, Cheshire, England":"Chester, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Spalding, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Spalding, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Basset, Lot-Et-Garonne, Aquitaine, France":"Basset, Lot-et-Garonne, Aquitaine, Ranska","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1070–1136":"1070–1136","1070–1096":"1070–1096","1092–1112":"1092–1112","1136":"1136","1112":"1112","1096":"1096","1070":"1070","1092":"1092","Skipton, Yorkshire, England":"Skipton, Everwyck, Angleterre","Chester, Cheshire, England":"Chester, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Spalding, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Spalding, Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Basset, Lot-Et-Garonne, Aquitaine, France":"Basset, Lot-et-Garonne, Aquitaine, France","Normandy, France":"Norma